vrRegEntry.name: vrRegEntry
vrRegEntry.description: An entry in the Voice Routing Group Table.

vrRegState.name: vrRegState
vrRegState.description: Current registration state. Options: vrOk (1): vrAgedOut (2): vrTableFull (3): vrMemallocFail (4): Default Value: None

vrRegVceStationId.name: vrRegVceStationId
vrRegVceStationId.description: Displays the Station ID name. Range of Values: From 0 to 15

vrRegVceSoftId.name: vrRegVceSoftId
vrRegVceSoftId.description: Displays the VCE software ID name. Range of Values: From 0 to 15 alphanumeric characters.

vrRegSlotNo.name: vrRegSlotNo
vrRegSlotNo.description: This parameter displays the slot number in which the VCE CPU resides. Range of Values: From 1 to 16 Default Value: None

vrRegHuntChannel.name: vrRegHuntChannel
vrRegHuntChannel.description: The string that represents the Hunt Channel number in 32 bits wide bit map in hexadecimal format. Range of Values: From 0 to 8

vrConfigNodeId.name: vrConfigNodeId
vrConfigNodeId.description: Allows you to create a unique name for the frame relay node. Range of Values: Up to 32 characters Default Value: VoiveRouting

vrConfigNoOfSysRouteSupported.name: vrConfigNoOfSysRouteSupported
vrConfigNoOfSysRouteSupported.description: Maximum number of routing definitions that can be supported in the VR table. Range of Values: From 1 to 1024 Default Value: 1

vrConfigNoOfDigitSupported.name: vrConfigNoOfDigitSupported
vrConfigNoOfDigitSupported.description: The maximum number of digits to be used for dial extension numbers over the entire network. Options: dig5 (5): The maximum number is five digits. dig7 (7): The maximum number is seven digits. (FOR FUTURE USE ONLY). Default Value: dig5 (5)

vrConfigMaxBufferPoolSize.name: vrConfigMaxBufferPoolSize
vrConfigMaxBufferPoolSize.description: Maximum number of OS buffers that can be queued at any time in the VR fifos. Range of Values: From 0 to 1000 Note: Zero (0) means that Voice/Fax packets are routed immediately (never queued). Default Values: 0

vrConfigFastSwitchingOption.name: vrConfigFastSwitchingOption
vrConfigFastSwitchingOption.description: This object refers to Dial Digit Packing for transmission of the extension numbers. The digits can be sent either 2 bytes or 4 bytes long. Options: vrprtysmall (1): The priority (using 2 bytes) is to minimize the amount of bandwidth used. This option is more CPU intensive, and slower. vrprtyroute (2): The priority (using 4 bytes) is speed. This option will minimize CPU usage but will require more bandwidth. Default Value: vrprtysmall (1)

vrConfigStatsSamplingPeriod.name: vrConfigStatsSamplingPeriod
vrConfigStatsSamplingPeriod.description: This parameter allows you to set the polling interval (in seconds) for statistics. Range of Values: From 0 to 3600 Default Value: 15

vrConfigControl.name: vrConfigControl
vrConfigControl.description: This object allows you to control the statistics in the VRSR table and the entries in the VR register table. Options: vrcfgidle(1): Control is turned off vrcfgrte(2): This option clears the statistics in the VRSR table. vrcfgreg(3): This options ages out the voice routing register of local extensions. Default Value: vrcfgidle (1)

vrConfigOptimization.name: vrConfigOptimization
vrConfigOptimization.description: This object allows you to enable and disable the optimization in the Voice, VR and FR modules. Options: vroptdisabled(1): Optimization code is turned off. This option enables backwards compatibility with older versions of VR software. This option will be removed in future releases. vroptenabled(2): Optimization code is turned on. This enables VR, Voice application module and Frame Relay Multiprotocol Encapsulation to use less bandwidth. this option will be removed in the future releases. vroptbwmgt(3): Optimization code is turned on plus enhancement for bandwidth management. This option is similar to option 2, in addition to when Bandwidth Management is enabled and there is no more bandwidth left on the link, then by chosing this option, it will stop any new voice call establishement. This is the default value and is the recommended value to use. Default Value: vroptbwmgt (3)

vrMibLevel.name: vrMibLevel
vrMibLevel.description: Used to determine current MIB module release supported by the agent. Object is in decimal.

vrStatInitState.name: vrStatInitState
vrStatInitState.description: VR module initialisation state. Options: vrDead (1): vrUnrecoverableError (2): vrTablesBuilt (3): vrConfigRead (4): vrInitialized (10)

vrStatLongestMuxPassInMs.name: vrStatLongestMuxPassInMs
vrStatLongestMuxPassInMs.description: Longest time recorded yet for a same multiplexing pass. Relevant only if pool is different from zero.

vrStatNbPacketsForwardedPerSec.name: vrStatNbPacketsForwardedPerSec
vrStatNbPacketsForwardedPerSec.description: No. of packets per second forwarded by VR during the last sampling period

vrStatNbRoutingConflicts.name: vrStatNbRoutingConflicts
vrStatNbRoutingConflicts.description: No.of times a routing conflict has been detected when adding a routing entry.

vrStatRegOverallNumber.name: vrStatRegOverallNumber
vrStatRegOverallNumber.description: Current number of local registration blocks.

vrStatRegNotOwner.name: vrStatRegNotOwner
vrStatRegNotOwner.description: Dial number not registered or refreshed because the requester is not owner of it.

vrStatRegInvalidDialNumber.name: vrStatRegInvalidDialNumber
vrStatRegInvalidDialNumber.description: The dial number is invalid and cannot be registered.

vrStatRegFormatError.name: vrStatRegFormatError
vrStatRegFormatError.description: Dial number not registered or refreshed because of a format error in the request.

vrStatNbVceMsgRx.name: vrStatNbVceMsgRx
vrStatNbVceMsgRx.description: Number of messages received from the VCE module.

vrStatNbVceMsgTx.name: vrStatNbVceMsgTx
vrStatNbVceMsgTx.description: Number of messages transmitted from the VCE module.

vrStatNbBusMsgRx.name: vrStatNbBusMsgRx
vrStatNbBusMsgRx.description: Number of messages received from the TBC module.

vrStatNbBusMsgTx.name: vrStatNbBusMsgTx
vrStatNbBusMsgTx.description: Number of messages transmitted from the TBC module.

vrStatNbWanMsgRx.name: vrStatNbWanMsgRx
vrStatNbWanMsgRx.description: Number of messages received from the WAN.

vrStatNbWanMsgTx.name: vrStatNbWanMsgTx
vrStatNbWanMsgTx.description: Number of messages transmitted from the WAN.

vrStatNbOutboundQueueFull.name: vrStatNbOutboundQueueFull
vrStatNbOutboundQueueFull.description: Number of times the buffer queue has been exceeded. (Irrelevant if pool is set to zero.)

vrStatNbOverallForwards.name: vrStatNbOverallForwards
vrStatNbOverallForwards.description: Number of overall packets (voice + other applications) forwarded.

vrStatNbOverallDiscards.name: vrStatNbOverallDiscards
vrStatNbOverallDiscards.description: Number of overall packets (voice + other applications) discarded.

vrStatNbDeadEnds.name: vrStatNbDeadEnds
vrStatNbDeadEnds.description: Number of times the routing process did not find any routing definition block for a specific dial number. This also increments the alldsc object.

vrStatError.name: vrStatError
vrStatError.description: Sum of many counters under vrStat.error.xxx, vrStat.ianIfError, etc.

vrStatFieldsAddress.name: vrStatFieldsAddress
vrStatFieldsAddress.description: vrStat starting address. Range of Values: From 0 to 10

vrStatIamUnxFieldAddress.name: vrStatIamUnxFieldAddress
vrStatIamUnxFieldAddress.description: IAM unexpected event table address. Range of Values: From 0 to 10

vrSrTable.name: vrSrTable
vrSrTable.description: The Voice Routing System Routes table.

vrSrEntry.name: vrSrEntry
vrSrEntry.description: An entry in the Voice Routing System Routes Table.

vrSrIndex.name: vrSrIndex
vrSrIndex.description: System route index. Range of Values: From 1 to 1024

vrSrRowStatus.name: vrSrRowStatus
vrSrRowStatus.description: Indicates whether this specific entry is configured within the MIB. Entries (rows) may be created by setting this object value to 'valid', or deleted by changing this object value to 'invalid'. Options: invalid (1): Entries can be deleted valid (2): Entries can be created

vrSrSubRef.name: vrSrSubRef
vrSrSubRef.description: Sub-reference number for multi-protocol encapsulation. Range of Values: From 1 to 31 Default Value: 1

vrSrBandwidth.name: vrSrBandwidth
vrSrBandwidth.description: Maximum Bandwidth allowed for the FR Link in Kbps. Note: If set to zero (0) bandwidth management is disabled

vrSrBwIndex.name: vrSrBwIndex
vrSrBwIndex.description: The index for bandwidth that corresponds to the vrBwEntry

vrSrStatus.name: vrSrStatus
vrSrStatus.description: Current VR system route status. Options: vrSrDown (1): vrSrInFlowCtl (2): vrSrUp (3):

vrSrConStatus.name: vrSrConStatus
vrSrConStatus.description: Current status of the connection establishment through IAM. Options: vrNotConfigured (1): vrClose (2): vrWaitForQuery (3): vrWaitForOpenConf (4): vrOpen (5):

vrSrFailStatus.name: vrSrFailStatus
vrSrFailStatus.description: Current fail status of the connection establishment through IAM. Options: vrNoFailure (1): vrInternalError (2): vrLocalMemFail (3): vrRemMemFail (4): vrRemNoAcces (5): vrRemPvcDown (6): vrRemPvcBusy (7): vrLocalFcnFailure (8): vrRemFcnFailure (9): vrLocalDsnFailure (10): vrRemAliasNotFound (11): vrNoPvcService (12): vrOpenReqTimeout (13): vrAdjaReset (14): vrUnsupportedSR (15):

vrSrNbLinkDown.name: vrSrNbLinkDown
vrSrNbLinkDown.description: The number of times that the system route has received a 'LINK_DOWN' with no route available notification.

vrSrNbOutboundFrame.name: vrSrNbOutboundFrame
vrSrNbOutboundFrame.description: Number of outbound frames (Voice/FAX, signaling and VR applications).

vrSrNbInboundFrame.name: vrSrNbInboundFrame
vrSrNbInboundFrame.description: Number of inbound frames (Voice/FAX, signaling and VR applications).

vrSrNbOutboundBw.name: vrSrNbOutboundBw
vrSrNbOutboundBw.description: Outbound WAN bandwidth required in BPS; this figure include the DLCI, the proprietary header for encapsulation (if used) and the CRC. The refresh period of that object depends on the stsmp object int the vrConfig group.

vrSrNbInboundBw.name: vrSrNbInboundBw
vrSrNbInboundBw.description: Inbound WAN bandwidth required in BPS; this figure include the DLCI, the proprietary header for encapsulation (if used) and the CRC. The refresh period of that object depends on the stsmp object int the vrConfig group.

vrSrBwUsed.name: vrSrBwUsed
vrSrBwUsed.description: The bandwidth utilized in kilo BPS. This value is shown only if the bandwith management for this Source Route is enabled.

vrSrNbCalls.name: vrSrNbCalls
vrSrNbCalls.description: The number of outstanding voice calls on this Vr Source Route. This value is shown only if the bandwith management for this Source Route is enabled.

vrSrNbPktDropped.name: vrSrNbPktDropped
vrSrNbPktDropped.description: The number of packets discarded due to Bandwidth management. When the bandwidth utilized on this VR Source Route reaches to its maximum bandwidth allowance, then this value represents the number of Voice packets discarded due to this fact.

vrRouteEntry.name: vrRouteEntry
vrRouteEntry.description: An entry in the Voice Routing Table.

vrRouteRowStatus.name: vrRouteRowStatus
vrRouteRowStatus.description: Indicates whether this specific entry is configured within the MIB. Entries (rows) may be created by setting this object value to 'valid', or deleted by changing this object value to 'invalid'. Options: invalid (1): Entries can be deleted valid (2): Entries can be created

vrRouteMask.name: vrRouteMask
vrRouteMask.description: The selection of the mask will dictate which of the digits will be read. A zero (0) means that the digit in that position will not be read. A one (1) means that the digit in that position will be read. Range of Values: 0000000 1000000 1100000 1110000 1111000 1111100 1111110 1111111 Default Value: 1111111

vrRouteSrNumber.name: vrRouteSrNumber
vrRouteSrNumber.description: VR system route number to use for the outbound traffic. Range of Values: From 1 to 1024

vrRouteForwardedPkt.name: vrRouteForwardedPkt
vrRouteForwardedPkt.description: The number of voice packets forwarded over the WAN.

vrPingDialNo.name: vrPingDialNo
vrPingDialNo.description: Dial number to ping. Range of Values: From 0 to 9999999

vrPingNbToBeSent.name: vrPingNbToBeSent
vrPingNbToBeSent.description: Number of pings to send after the trigger. (4,000,000 would mean one packet sent every 24 ms for 24 hours). 0 means stop the current ping session. Range of Values: From 0 to 4,000,000 Default Value: 1

vrPingGapsInMs.name: vrPingGapsInMs
vrPingGapsInMs.description: The interval in milliseconds between ping frames. Range of Values: From 0 to 1000 Default Value: 24

vrPingMaxHopCount.name: vrPingMaxHopCount
vrPingMaxHopCount.description: Maximum Hop count allowed. Range of Values: From 1 to 256 Default Value: 16

vrPingProbeReturnAddress.name: vrPingProbeReturnAddress
vrPingProbeReturnAddress.description: Probe (i.e. ping/trace/search) return dial number. Range of Values: From 0 to 9999999 Default Value: 9999999

vrPingTriggerSend.name: vrPingTriggerSend
vrPingTriggerSend.description: Trigger the pings to be sent. Options: vrIdle (1): No pings are sent vrSend (2): The counter is set to zero and pings will be sent

vrPingNbReplyRx.name: vrPingNbReplyRx
vrPingNbReplyRx.description: Count the number of ping replies received

vrPingFormatError.name: vrPingFormatError
vrPingFormatError.description: Count the number of non-recognizable ping replies.

vrPingNbVrNodesCrossedForward.name: vrPingNbVrNodesCrossedForward
vrPingNbVrNodesCrossedForward.description: The number of nodes hopped outbound (forward). When compared to the number of hops inbound (backward) the difference can help trace the path.

vrPingNbVrNodesCrossedBackward.name: vrPingNbVrNodesCrossedBackward
vrPingNbVrNodesCrossedBackward.description: The number of nodes hopped inbound (Backward). When compared to the number of hops outbound (forward) the difference can help trace the path.

vrPingLastRoundTripInMs.name: vrPingLastRoundTripInMs
vrPingLastRoundTripInMs.description: The time in milliseconds that the ping took for its last round-trip.

vrPingLastSequenceNumberRx.name: vrPingLastSequenceNumberRx
vrPingLastSequenceNumberRx.description: The sequence number of the last ping received.

vrPingSequenceError.name: vrPingSequenceError
vrPingSequenceError.description: The sequence number of the last error received. Not available if the number of pings is set to one.

vrPingMinRoundTripInMs.name: vrPingMinRoundTripInMs
vrPingMinRoundTripInMs.description: The Minimum round trip time in milliseconds. This is not applicable if pinging is set to one (1).

vrPingMaxRoundTripInMs.name: vrPingMaxRoundTripInMs
vrPingMaxRoundTripInMs.description: the Maximum round trip time in milliseconds. this is not applicable if pinging is set to one (1).

vrPingRemStatus.name: vrPingRemStatus
vrPingRemStatus.description: The ping returns the status of the remote node. Options: vrOk (1): The remote is OK vrUnknown (5): Status unknown, there is no response.

vrPingRemVrNodeId.name: vrPingRemVrNodeId
vrPingRemVrNodeId.description: Displays the remote node ID. Range of Values: From 0 to 31

vrPingRemVceStationId.name: vrPingRemVceStationId
vrPingRemVceStationId.description: Displays the remote VCE station ID. Range of Values: from 0 to 15

vrPingRemVrSoftId.name: vrPingRemVrSoftId
vrPingRemVrSoftId.description: Displays the remote VR software version number. Range of Values: From 0 to 3

vrPingRemVceSoftId.name: vrPingRemVceSoftId
vrPingRemVceSoftId.description: Displays the remote VCE software version number.

vrPingRemSlotIndex.name: vrPingRemSlotIndex
vrPingRemSlotIndex.description: The remote VCE slot number of the registered number

vrPingRemHuntChannel.name: vrPingRemHuntChannel
vrPingRemHuntChannel.description: Displays the remote hunt channel number. Range of Values: From 0 to 8

vrPingRemNbForwardedPacket.name: vrPingRemNbForwardedPacket
vrPingRemNbForwardedPacket.description: Number of forwarded packets using that route definition block.

vrPingRemNbRestart.name: vrPingRemNbRestart
vrPingRemNbRestart.description: No of times the attached VCE has restarted.

vrBwTable.description: The Voice Routing Bandwidth Management table.

vrBwEntry.name: vrBwEntry
vrBwEntry.description: An entry in the Voice Routing Bandwidth Management Table.

vrBwIndex.name: vrBwIndex
vrBwIndex.description: Total bandwidth index. Range of Values: From 1 to 32

vrBwRowStatus.description: Indicates whether this specific entry is configured within the MIB. Options: invalid (1): Entries can be deleted valid (2): Entries can be created

vrBwBandwidthCfg.name: vrBwBandwidthCfg
vrBwBandwidthCfg.description: Maximum Bandwidth allowed for the FR Link in Kbps. Note: If set to zero (0) bandwidth management is disabled Default: 0 (disabled) Range of Values: From 0 to 65535

vrBwBandwidthUsed.description: Total bandwidth used on the FR Link in Kbps. Range of Values: From 0 to 65535

vrBwNbCalls.description: Total number of outstanding Voice sessions on that FR Link Range of Values: From 0 to 65535
